<Page
    x:Class="CatholicHymnBookUWP.Views.RosaryPage"
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
    xmlns:local="using:CatholicHymnBookUWP.Views"
    xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
    xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
    mc:Ignorable="d">

    <Page.Transitions>
        <TransitionCollection>
            <NavigationThemeTransition />
        </TransitionCollection>
    </Page.Transitions>
    
    <!-- Content -->
    <Grid Background="{ThemeResource ApplicationPageBackgroundThemeBrush}">
        <Pivot x:Name="RosaryPivot">
            <PivotItem x:Name="Joyful" Header="Joyful Mysteries" >
                <ScrollViewer>
                    <Grid>
                        <ScrollViewer>
                            <StackPanel>
                                <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Joyful-1.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                                <RichTextBlock Margin="0,15,20,20">
                                    <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                        1.
                                        <Bold>The Annunciation</Bold> - The angel Gabriel brings word
                                            from God that Mary is to be the Mother of our Saviour.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                    <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray for oppenness to God's word and inspiration
                                            and for a readiness to follow his call.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </RichTextBlock>
                                <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Joyful-2.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                                <RichTextBlock Margin="0,10,20,20">
                                    <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                        2.
                                        <Bold>The Visitation</Bold> - Mary helps Elizabeth in her 
                                            preparations for the birth of John the Baptist.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                    <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray for an open eye for the needs of others.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </RichTextBlock>
                                <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Joyful-3.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                                <RichTextBlock Margin="0,15,20,20">
                                    <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                        3.
                                        <Bold>The Birth of Jesus</Bold> - Jesus is born in very poor 
                                            circumstances in Bethlehem where people showed no hospitality to Mary and Joseph.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                    <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray for newly born children that they may experience
                                            the love of their parents and relatives.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </RichTextBlock>
                                <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Joyful-4.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                                <RichTextBlock Margin="0,20,20,20">
                                    <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                        4.
                                        <Bold>The Presentation of Jesus in the Temple</Bold> - Mary and Joseph 
                                            offer their child to God in accordance with the law of Moses.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                    <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray for vocations and for the young men and women ready
                                            to dedicate themselves totally to the service of God.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </RichTextBlock>
                                <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Joyful-5.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                                <RichTextBlock Margin="0,20,20,20">
                                    <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                        5.
                                        <Bold>The Finding of Jesus in the Temple</Bold> - Mary and Joseph find 
                                            Jesus discussing the 'things of his Father' in the temple after they had searched for three days.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                    <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray that parents may constantly have their children's 
                                            welfare at heart.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </RichTextBlock>
                            </StackPanel>
                        </ScrollViewer>
                    </Grid>
                </ScrollViewer>
            </PivotItem>
            <PivotItem x:Name="Sorrowful" Header="Sorrowful Mysteries">
                <Grid>
                    <ScrollViewer>
                        <StackPanel>
                            <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Sorrowful-1.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                            <RichTextBlock Margin="0,15,20,20">
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                    1.
                                    <Bold>The Agony of Jesus in the Garden</Bold> - Jesus is afraid to drink
                                            the chalice which the Father gives him to drink, but he is strengthened by an angel.
                                </Paragraph>
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray that we may receive God's strength to face the trial
                                            of life.
                                </Paragraph>
                            </RichTextBlock>
                            <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Sorrowful-2.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                            <RichTextBlock Margin="0,10,20,20">
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                    2.
                                    <Bold>The Scourging of Jesus at the Pillar</Bold> - Even though Pilate 
                                            recognizes the innocence of Jesus he has him scourged by the soldiers.
                                </Paragraph>
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray that we may never hurt our neighbour, neither by word
                                            nor by deed.
                                </Paragraph>
                            </RichTextBlock>
                            <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Sorrowful-3.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                            <RichTextBlock Margin="0,15,20,20">
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                    3.
                                    <Bold>The Crowning of Jesus with a Crown of Thorns</Bold> - Jesus is publicly
                                            humiliated and insulted by the soldiers who play the fool with him.
                                </Paragraph>
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray that we may follow Christ even when this means accepting
                                            insults and mockery.
                                </Paragraph>
                            </RichTextBlock>
                            <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Sorrowful-4.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                            <RichTextBlock Margin="0,20,20,20">
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                    4.
                                    <Bold>Jesus Carries His Cross to Calvary</Bold> - Jesus takes up the cross 
                                            because he knows it is the will of his father.
                                </Paragraph>
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray that we may see our daily problems and hardships a way
                                            of following in the footsteps of Christ.
                                </Paragraph>
                            </RichTextBlock>
                            <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Sorrowful-5.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                            <RichTextBlock Margin="0,20,20,20">
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                    5.
                                    <Bold>Jesus Dies on the Cross</Bold> - Jesus dies after having entrusted his
                                            followers into the care of Mary, his mother.
                                </Paragraph>
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray that we may live and die for the greater honour and glory
                                            of God.
                                </Paragraph>
                            </RichTextBlock>
                        </StackPanel>
                    </ScrollViewer>
                </Grid>
            </PivotItem>
            <PivotItem x:Name="Glorious" Header="Glorious Mysteries">
                <Grid>
                    <ScrollViewer>
                        <StackPanel>
                            <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Glorious-1.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                            <RichTextBlock Margin="0,15,20,20">
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                    1.
                                    <Bold>The Resurrection</Bold> - Jesus is glorified by the Father and rises
                                            to a new life.
                                </Paragraph>
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray for a greater awareness of the risen Christ in our lives.
                                </Paragraph>
                            </RichTextBlock>
                            <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Glorious-2.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                            <RichTextBlock Margin="0,20,20,20">
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                    2.
                                    <Bold>The Ascension of Jesus into Heaven</Bold> - Jesus is taken away from
                                            the sight of the apostles, whom he told to prepare themselves for the coming of another Helper.
                                </Paragraph>
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray that our church leaders may always faithfully carry on the
                                            work started by Jesus.
                                </Paragraph>
                            </RichTextBlock>
                            <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Glorious-3.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                            <RichTextBlock Margin="0,20,20,20">
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                    3.
                                    <Bold>The Descent of the Holy Spirit</Bold> - Mary and the disciples receive the
                                            Holy Spirit who enables them to spread the good news throughout the world.
                                </Paragraph>
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray that we Christians may never be afraid to openly profess our
                                            faith.
                                </Paragraph>
                            </RichTextBlock>
                            <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Glorious-4.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                            <RichTextBlock Margin="0,20,20,20">
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                    4.
                                    <Bold>Mary is taken up into Heaven</Bold> - Mary is taken up body and sul into heaven.
                                </Paragraph>
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray that our lives may be directed toward our final union with Christ
                                            in heaven.
                                </Paragraph>
                            </RichTextBlock>
                            <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Glorious-5.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                            <RichTextBlock Margin="0,20,20,20">
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                    5.
                                    <Bold>Crowning of Mary in Heaven</Bold> - Mary receives a glorious reward for her complete 
                                            devotion to God.
                                </Paragraph>
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray that the hope of receiving an imperishable crown, may help us to carry
                                            on in times of hardships.
                                </Paragraph>
                            </RichTextBlock>
                        </StackPanel>
                    </ScrollViewer>
                </Grid>
            </PivotItem>
            <PivotItem x:Name="Luminous" Header="Luminous Mysteries">
                <Grid>
                    <ScrollViewer>
                        <StackPanel>
                            <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Luminous-1.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                            <RichTextBlock Margin="0,15,20,20">
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                    1.
                                    <Bold>The Baptism of Jesus</Bold> - While Jesus was baptised by John in the Jordan,
                                            the Holy Spirit descended upon him in the form of a dove.
                                </Paragraph>
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray that all those who are reborn in Baptism may remain faithful to 
                                            their baptismal promises and allow the Holy Spirit to guide them in life.
                                </Paragraph>
                            </RichTextBlock>
                            <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Luminous-2.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                            <RichTextBlock Margin="0,0,20,20">
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                    2.
                                    <Bold>The Wedding Feast at Cana</Bold> - During the wedding feast at Cana, Jesus perdormed
                                            his first miracle: he changed water into wine.
                                </Paragraph>
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray that those who are facing problems in life may go to Jesus for help and 
                                            inspiration.
                                </Paragraph>
                            </RichTextBlock>
                            <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Luminous-3.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                            <RichTextBlock Margin="0,20,20,20">
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                    3.
                                    <Bold>The Proclamation of the Kingdom</Bold> - Jesus begins his public life with the proclamation:
                                    <Italic>"the kingdom of God is at hand; repent and believe the Gospel"</Italic>
                                </Paragraph>
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray for all those who are called to proclaim the gospel, that they may proclaim it
                                            failthfully and that the faithful may repent and experience God's power and salvation.
                                </Paragraph>
                            </RichTextBlock>
                            <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Luminous-4.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                            <RichTextBlock Margin="0,20,20,20">
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                    4.
                                    <Bold>The Transfiguration</Bold> - During the Transfiguration Jesus showed his glory to the Apostles
                                            Peter, James and John, while God the father said:
                                    <Italic>"this is my beloved Son, listen to him"</Italic>
                                </Paragraph>
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray that God may give all of us the commitment to listen to the Good News proclaimed
                                            by Jesus and turn away from those transpired by the Evil One.
                                </Paragraph>
                            </RichTextBlock>
                            <Image Source="ms-appx:///Assets/Luminous-5.png" Height="180" Width="180"  />
                            <RichTextBlock Margin="0,20,20,20">
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,5">
                                    5.
                                    <Bold>The Institution of the Eucharist</Bold> - During the Last Supper Jesus gave us the greatest sign 
                                            of his love, his own Body and Blood, to strengthen us on our journey through life.
                                </Paragraph>
                                <Paragraph FontSize="18" TextAlignment="Justify" Margin="0,0,0,20">- We pray that all followers of Christ may come to him and eat his Body and drink his blood,
                                            so that he can strengthen them in all circumstances of life.
                                </Paragraph>
                            </RichTextBlock>
                        </StackPanel>
                    </ScrollViewer>
                </Grid>
            </PivotItem>
        </Pivot>
    </Grid>
</Page>
